			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I would like to reconfirm the correct posts here and help sort out the trash.  The small 3rd floor room with the torture rack above a spiral staircase is the spawn spot.  The spawn rate is 50-55 minutes roughly.  The vast majority of the spawns are a regular ghoul (low green to anyone camping this, dies very quickly and didn't aggro me at 35 unless I was medding).  Very rarely Preist of Najena spawns.  The one time I finally saw him spawn, he killed me 2 times before he went down.  When he killed me, I came back in the zone and found him back at his spawn point by the time I had looted my corpse, so I don't think he wanders unless trained.  He's blue to me at 35, but he's a toughie for a wiz to solo.  Bring a second person along and you should be fine.  Also - he finally died when a nice group finished him off after he killed me the second time, but someone else ninja'd the loot they left for me - another good reason to have a freind with you.  For the one spawn of Preist that I've seen, so far I've seen about 10 ghoul spawns, so it may be fairly rare.
